From: gcc-for-Windows98
Subject: [PATCH] config_tccdir_w32: resolve resources at ../tcc relative to tcc.exe

The extras toolset packages tcc.exe in a SHARED bin/ directory next to
gcc/binutils/busybox/etc., so we can't install tcc's headers + libtcc1.a
+ *.def under bin/ as sibling subdirs without polluting the bin/ namespace.
Move tcc's resources to <prefix>/tcc/ (sibling of bin/) and patch the
runtime tccdir resolver to append "/../tcc" to the dirname of tcc.exe.

Before: tccdir = dirname(tcc.exe) = <prefix>/bin
After:  tccdir = dirname(tcc.exe) + "/../tcc" = <prefix>/bin/../tcc
        (CreateFile / fopen downstream collapse the "../" segment, so
        actual resource lookups land at <prefix>/tcc/{include,lib,libtcc}.)

The change is contained in config_tccdir_w32 — it only fires when
CONFIG_TCCDIR isn't pre-baked at build time, which is our case for
--targetos=WIN32 builds.  Buffer is MAX_PATH (260); appended literal is
8 bytes — safe under any practical install path on Win98 (FAT32's path
length cap is well below MAX_PATH).

diff --git a/libtcc.c b/libtcc.c
--- a/libtcc.c
+++ b/libtcc.c
@@ -111,6 +111,14 @@ static inline char *config_tccdir_w32(char *path)
     if (p > path)
         --p;
     *p = 0;
+    /* gcc-for-Windows98 layout: tcc.exe lives in <prefix>/bin/ but its
+       headers, libtcc1.a, *.def, libtcc.a, libtcc.h live in <prefix>/tcc/
+       — out of the shared bin/ directory.  Append "/../tcc" so resource
+       lookups (tcc_add_sysinclude_path / tcc_add_library_path) land at
+       <prefix>/tcc/.  Path ops downstream (CreateFile / fopen) collapse
+       the "../" segment.  Buffer is MAX_PATH (260); appended literal is
+       8 bytes — safe under any practical install path. */
+    strcat(path, "/../tcc");
     return path;
 }
 #define CONFIG_TCCDIR config_tccdir_w32(alloca(MAX_PATH))
